## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **HTML5 + CSS3 + Vanilla JavaScript** — zero frameworks, zero dependencies
- **[Jikan API v4](https://jikan.moe)** — free unofficial MyAnimeList REST API
- **Web Notifications API** — native browser notifications
- **localStorage** — client-side persistence for pinned anime
- **Google Fonts** — Bebas Neue + Inter + JetBrains Mono

---

## ⚡ Quick Start

### Option 1 — Just open the file
```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/shri778/animeverse.git
cd animeverse

# Open directly in browser — no server needed!
open animeverse.html
```

### Option 2 — Local server (recommended)
```bash
# Using Python
python -m http.server 8000

# Using Node.js
npx serve .
```
Then open `http://localhost:8000`

---

## 🌐 Deploy for Free

### Netlify (Recommended)
1. Go to [netlify.com](https://netlify.com) → Sign up free
2. Drag and drop the project folder
3. Done — live in 30 seconds ✅

### GitHub Pages
1. Push this repo to GitHub
2. Go to **Settings → Pages → Source → main branch**
3. Your site: `https://yourusername.github.io/animeverse`

### Vercel
```bash
npx vercel
```

---

## 📌 How Notifications Work

1. Click **"Enable Notifications"** on the homepage
2. Allow the browser permission prompt
3. Pin any anime using the 🔖 button
4. A **real browser notification** fires instantly:

```
📌 AnimeVerse — Anime Pinned!
You pinned "Attack on Titan". We'll notify you about new episodes!
```

> **Note:** Notifications work on Chrome, Firefox, Edge, and Android browsers. iOS Safari has limited support.

